<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0113">
<l>aioṭu kuiṉatukaṇ ṇeṉṉu</l>
<l>mavvā ṟeṉpa vēṟṟumai yurupē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Words, juxtaposed in case-relation,<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">vēṟṟumai kuṟitta</foreign></note> ' relation designed as case '</l>
<l>as well as words juxtaposed in non-case relation,<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">vēṟṟumai yalvaḻi</foreign></note> ' non-case relation '.</l>
<l>have either a sound<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu.</foreign></note> or an empty-morph,<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">cāriyai.</foreign></note></l>
<l>one of the two, inserted,</l>
<l>when sandhi takes place.</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">ai oṭu ku iṉ atu kaṇ,</foreign></l>
<l>those six are said to be case-morphs.<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">vēṟṟumaiyurupu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
